get.description: Retrieves information about the Claris FileMaker Server or Claris FileMaker Cloud host
Retrieve a list of hosted FileMaker databases.

post.description:
Login to a FileMaker database.
Provide either an 'Authorization' header parameter OR BOTH 'X-FM-Data-OAuth-Request-Id' and 'X-FM-Data-OAuth-Identifier' header parameters.

fmDataSource.description:
External FileMaker Data Source Authentication:

{"fmDataSource": [ { "database": "<databaseName>", "username" : "<username>", "password" : "<password>", "oAuthRequestId" : "<oAuthRequestId>", "oAuthIdentifier" : "<oAuthIdentifier>"} ] }

"database": is a string with the name of the external database file.

"username": is a string with the username to login to solution.

"password": is a string with the password to login to solution.

"oAuthRequestId": is the X-FMS-Request-ID header value returned from '/oauth/getoauthurl' in FileMaker Server OAuth workflow.

"oAuthIdentifier": is the URL query value for "identifier" in FileMaker Server OAuth workflow.

(NOTE: If both "oAuthRequestId" and "oAuthIdentifier" are supplied, FileMaker Data API will perform an OAuth login.)

(NOTE: This feature only supports databases hosted on the same FileMaker Server.)

Retrieves a list of scripts for a FileMaker database
Retrieves layout metadata for a FileMaker database.

parameters.name: _offset
parameters.description: The record number of the first record in the range of records.

parameters.name: _limit
parameters.description: The maximum number of records that should be returned. If not specified, the default value is 100.

parameters.name: _sort
parameters.description: Field name and sort order of the result set. The order in which the criteria are specified determines the precedence. Records are returned in the original creation order if a sort order is not provided. The default sort order is "ascend".

parameters.name: dateformats
parameters.description: The date format. Use 0 for US, 1 for file locale, or 2 for ISO8601. If not specified, the default value is 0.

fieldData.description: A JSON object that contains field-value pairs for fields in the target layout. If "{}" is provided as a data value, an empty record is created with any auto enter values defined in the current table’s schema.

options.description: Options to control the creation of records.

entrymode.description: The data entry mode. Use "script" to override a field's "Allow user to override during data entry" option, or "user" to follow the field option. The default is "user".

prohibitmode.description: The prohibit modification mode. Use the "script" option to ignore the auto-entry rule "Prohibit modification of value during data entry" option, or "user" to follow the rules. The default is "user".

portalData.description: A JSON object that contains portal row values in the target layout. The format mirrors the portalData format from Get Records.
